ontologyFramework.OFRunning.OFInitialising

Class OFBuilderCommon

  • java.lang.Object
    • ontologyFramework.OFRunning.OFInitialising.OFBuilderCommon

  • public class OFBuilderCommon
extends java.lang.Object

    This is a static class (set as non instanciable) which collects static methods useful during the system initialisation through builder mechanism. Especially in OFInitialiser.buildIndividual(OWLNamedIndividual, OWLReferences)

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Buoncomapgni Luca
    See Also:
    OFInitialiser, OFBuilderInterface, KeyWordsMapper, NameMapper, OFDebugLogger

    • Field Detail

      • CLASSPACKAGE_objProp

        public static final java.lang.String CLASSPACKAGE_objProp
        represents the name of the Object Property which link a builder individual to its Java class. It links to an individual which belongs to the "Name" ontological class. For this it represents a string which has the complete.java.class.package path to a class that implements OFBuilderInterface. By default it is equal to "hasTypeName"
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • BUILDLISTNAME_objProp

        public static final java.lang.String BUILDLISTNAME_objProp
        represents the name of the Object Property which link a builder individual to its initialised class inside the Map. It links to an individual which belongs to the "Name" ontological class. For this, it represents a string which is the key to refer to the output of OFBuilderInterface.getInitialisedClasses() from the class OFBuildedListInvoker. By default it is equal to "buildsList"
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • HASKEYWORDS_objProp

        public static final java.lang.String HASKEYWORDS_objProp
        represents the name of the Object Property which link a builder individual to the key words that we want inject inside the method OFBuilderInterface.buildInfo(String[], OWLReferences, OFBuildedListInvoker). It links to an individual which belongs to the "KeyWord" ontological class. For this, it represents an array of strings which. By default it is equal to "hasKeyWords"
        See Also:

      • CONSOLEFLAG_dataProp

        public static final java.lang.String CONSOLEFLAG_dataProp
        It is the name of the data propriety which indicates that the system should print on console. If it is attached to an individual which belongs to the ontological class "Debugger". By default it is set to: "hasDebuggingPrintOnConsole"

      • GUIFLAG_dataProp

        public static final java.lang.String GUIFLAG_dataProp
        It is the name of the data propriety which indicates that the system should show the GUI on start up. If it is attached to an individual which belongs to the ontological class "Debugger". By default it is set to: "hasDebuggingRunGui"
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PRINTRATE_dataProp

        public static final java.lang.String PRINTRATE_dataProp
        It is the name of the data propriety which indicates that the system should update the file and show log when their count reach this determinate threshold. If it is attached to an individual which belongs to the ontological class "Debugger". By default it is set to: "hasDebuggingOrderPrintRate". Note that if the system is brutally shotted down, some logging text could be still buffered; and they would not be notified.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • getKeyWords

        public static java.lang.String[] getKeyWords(org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual individual,
                             OWLReferences ontoRef)
        It maps the literal, described as a keyWord in the ontology, linked to the builder individual.
        Parameters:
        individual - ontological individual which belongs to OFInitialiser.BUILDER_className class
        ontoRef - reference to the ontology in which the individual is belong to
        Returns:
        keyWords mapped keyWords from Literal to String[] Given an individual which represents the builder it gets the individual which describe the keyWord, through the Object Property defined by the name HASKEYWORDS_objProp. This, by default has the value "hasKeyWords". Than, this methods uses KeyWordsMapper.getKeyWordFromOntology(OWLNamedIndividual, OWLReferences) to map the actual literal into an array of String. 
                BuilderIndividual € OFBuilder          [ please refer to ... OFInitialiser]
                hasKeyWords exactly 1 KeyWordInd
                        where:  KeyWordInd € KeyWord
                                                KeyWordInd hasTypeKeyWord "key1 key2 key3"^^string

      • buildDebugger

        public static void buildDebugger(org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual individual,
                 OFBuildedListInvoker listInvoker,
                 OWLReferences ontoRef)
        It initialises the main debugging property
        Parameters:
        individual - which defines the debugging Property
        listInvoker - to retrieve already builded classes
        ontoRef - the reference to the ontology in which the individual belongs to. It initialises the class OFDebugLogger with the information stored in the only (if more are available one will be picked up) individual belong to the ontological class "DebuggedClass" (where its name is described by: DebuggingClassFlagData.DEBUGGER_classFlags). In particular, given an individual X, it makes four steps: 
                1 -> get the only individual attached to X trough 
                                CONSOLEFLAG_dataProp, which has value "hasDebuggingPrintOnConsole". 
                                Compute the boolean value and uses it to call
                                OFDebugLogger.setPrintOnConsole(Boolean)
        
        2 -> get the only individual attached to X trough
                                FILEFLAG_dataProp, which has value "hasDebuggingPrintOnFile".
                                Compute the string value and uses it to call
                                OFDebugLogger.setPrintOnFile(String)
 
  3 -> get the only individual attached to X trough
                                PRINTRATE_dataProp, which has value "hasDebuggingOrderPrintRate".
                                Compute the integer value and uses it to call
                                OFDebugLogger.setOrderPrintingRate(Integer)
 
  4 -> get the only individual attached to X trough
                                GUIFLAG_dataProp, which has value "hasDebuggingRunGui".
                                Compute the boolean value and uses it to start the GUI
